-- Calculate the gap between the highest and lowest average salary
WITH salary_gap AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS gap
    FROM district
),
-- Find the account numbers of the oldest female client with the lowest average salary
oldest_female AS (
    SELECT a.account_id
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON c.client_id = a.account_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
    ORDER BY c.birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
)
-- Combine the results
SELECT of.account_id, sg.gap
FROM oldest_female of, salary_gap sg;

    FROM atom

    SELECT element
    FROM ElementCounts
    ORDER BY atom_count DESC
    LIMIT 1

    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b.bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM atom a
    INNER JOIN bond b ON a.molecule_id = b.molecule_id
    WHERE a.element = (SELECT element FROM MostCommonElement)
),

-- Step 3: Calculate the percentage
TotalAtoms AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_atom_count
    FROM atom
)

FROM

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of carcinogenic molecules with triple bonded H atoms
WITH TripleBondedMolecules AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT m.molecule_id
    FROM molecule m
    INNER JOIN atom a ON m.molecule_id = a.molecule_id
    INNER JOIN bond b ON m.molecule_id = b.molecule_id
    WHERE a.element = 'h' AND b.bond_type = '#'
      AND m.label = '+'
),
TotalCarcinogenicMolecules AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_carcinogenic
    FROM molecule
    WHERE label = '+'
)
SELECT 
    (CAST(COUNT(TBM.molecule_id) AS REAL) / TCM.total_carcinogenic) * 100.0 AS percentage
FROM TripleBondedMolecules TBM, TotalCarcinogenicMolecules TCM;

-- Part 1: Annual average number of sets released between 1/1/2012 and 12/31/2015
WITH SetCounts AS (
    SELECT
        strftime('%Y', releaseDate) AS year,
        COUNT(*) AS setCount
    FROM sets
    WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY year
),
AverageSets AS (
    SELECT
        AVG(setCount) AS avgSets
    FROM SetCounts
)

-- Part 2: Determine the common language
, LanguageCounts AS (
    SELECT
        fd.language,
        COUNT(*) AS languageCount
    FROM sets s
    INNER JOIN foreign_data fd ON s.code = fd.multiverseid
    WHERE s.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY fd.language
),
CommonLanguage AS (
    SELECT
        language
    FROM LanguageCounts
    WHERE languageCount = (SELECT MAX(languageCount) FROM LanguageCounts)
)

-- Combine Results
SELECT
    avgSets,
    language AS commonLanguage
FROM AverageSets, CommonLanguage;

WITH RaceInfo AS (
    SELECT raceId
    FROM races
    WHERE name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND year = 2008
),
ChampionTime AS (
    SELECT time AS champion_time
    FROM results
    INNER JOIN RaceInfo ON results.raceId = RaceInfo.raceId
    WHERE position = 1
),
IncrementalTime AS (
    SELECT 
        time,
        LAG(time) OVER (ORDER BY time) AS incremental_time
    FROM results
    INNER JOIN RaceInfo ON results.raceId = RaceInfo.raceId
),
LastDriverTime AS (
    SELECT 
        incremental_time + champion_time AS last_driver_time
    FROM IncrementalTime, ChampionTime
    WHERE incremental_time IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT 
    (CAST(strftime('%s', champion_time) AS REAL) - CAST(strftime('%s', incremental_time) AS REAL)) / 
    CAST(strftime('%s', last_driver_time) AS REAL) * 100 AS percentage_faster
FROM IncrementalTime, LastDriverTime, ChampionTime
WHERE incremental_time IS NOT NULL;

-- SQL Query to Calculate Differences in Annual Average Consumption
WITH LowestConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        MIN(y.Consumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'CZK'
        AND y.Date LIKE '2013%'
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
TotalConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
        COUNT(DISTINCT c.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'CZK'
        AND y.Date LIKE '2013%'
        AND (c.Segment, y.Consumption) IN (
            SELECT
                Segment,
                MinConsumption
            FROM
                LowestConsumption
        )
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        TotalConsumption / CustomerCount AS AnnualAverage
    FROM
        TotalConsumption
)
SELECT
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS LAMvsKAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS KAMvsSME;

WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013 AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM
        SegmentConsumption
    WHERE
        Consumption2013 > 0 -- Avoid division by zero
)
SELECT
    MAX(PercentageIncrease) AS MaxPercentageIncrease,
    MIN(PercentageIncrease) AS MinPercentageIncrease
FROM
    PercentageIncrease;
